{
  "name": "FTC-WF-002_pipeline-sponsor",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## FTC-WF-002 Pipeline de Sponsors\n\n**Descripcion**: Monitorea cambios de estado en el pipeline de sponsors y ejecuta acciones automatizadas segun la etapa.\n\n**Owner**: Equipo Comercial / Ops FinteChile\n\n**Fecha de creacion**: 2025-02-18\n\n**Version**: 1.0.0\n\n**Folder**: /Core\n\n**Criticidad**: Alta\n\n---\n\n**Env vars requeridas**:\n- `NOTION_DB_SPONSORS_ID`\n- `NOTION_DB_TAREAS_ID`\n- `SLACK_CHANNEL_EJECUTIVO`\n- `SLACK_CHANNEL_OPS`\n- `EMAIL_FROM`\n- `DRIVE_FOLDER_MIEMBROS_ID`\n\n**Credenciales**:\n- Notion account\n- Gmail account\n- Slack account\n- Google Drive account",
        "height": 480,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "sticky-metadata",
      "name": "Workflow Metadata",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -200,
        -100
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "minutes",
              "minutesInterval": 5
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "schedule-trigger",
      "name": "Schedule Trigger",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        280,
        300
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "resource": "databasePage",
        "operation": "getAll",
        "databaseId": {
          "__rl": true,
          "mode": "id",
          "value": "={{ $env.NOTION_DB_SPONSORS_ID }}"
        },
        "returnAll": false,
        "limit": 50,
        "filterType": "formula",
        "formula": "{{ { \"and\": [ { \"timestamp\": \"last_edited_time\", \"last_edited_time\": { \"past_week\": {} } } ] } }}",
        "options": {}
      },
      "id": "notion-query-sponsors",
      "name": "Query Sponsors Pipeline",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.notion",
      "typeVersion": 2.2,
      "position": [
        500,
        300
      ],
      "credentials": {
        "notionApi": {
          "id": "",
          "name": "Notion account"
        }
      },
      "notes": "Query Notion DB 'Sponsors Pipeline' for recently modified records. Uses last_edited_time filter. Env var: NOTION_DB_SPONSORS_ID"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "// FTC-WF-002: Filtrar registros donde el Estado cambio respecto al Estado_Anterior\n// Solo procesar si el estado actual difiere del estado anterior almacenado\n\nconst items = $input.all();\nconst changedItems = [];\n\nfor (const item of items) {\n  const props = item.json.properties || item.json;\n\n  // Extraer Estado actual y Estado_Anterior\n  // Ajustar nombres de propiedad segun schema real de Notion\n  const estadoActual = props.Estado?.select?.name\n    || props.Estado?.status?.name\n    || props['Estado']?.select?.name\n    || '';\n\n  const estadoAnterior = props.Estado_Anterior?.rich_text?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || props['Estado_Anterior']?.rich_text?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || props.Estado_Anterior?.select?.name\n    || '';\n\n  // Extraer datos utiles del sponsor\n  const sponsorName = props.Name?.title?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || props.Nombre?.title?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || props.Empresa?.title?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || 'Sin nombre';\n\n  const ownerEmail = props.Owner?.people?.[0]?.person?.email\n    || props.Responsable?.people?.[0]?.person?.email\n    || '';\n\n  const ownerName = props.Owner?.people?.[0]?.name\n    || props.Responsable?.people?.[0]?.name\n    || '';\n\n  const contactEmail = props.Email?.email\n    || props.Contacto_Email?.email\n    || '';\n\n  const contactName = props.Contacto?.rich_text?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || props.Nombre_Contacto?.rich_text?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || '';\n\n  const pageId = item.json.id || '';\n\n  const lossReason = props.Motivo_Perdida?.select?.name\n    || props.Motivo_Perdida?.rich_text?.[0]?.plain_text\n    || 'No especificado';\n\n  // Solo incluir si hay cambio de estado\n  if (estadoActual && estadoActual !== estadoAnterior) {\n    changedItems.push({\n      json: {\n        pageId,\n        sponsorName,\n        estadoActual,\n        estadoAnterior,\n        ownerEmail,\n        ownerName,\n        contactEmail,\n        contactName,\n        lossReason,\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString()\n      }\n    });\n  }\n}\n\n// Si no hay cambios, retornar array vacio para detener el flujo\nif (changedItems.length === 0) {\n  return [{ json: { noChanges: true } }];\n}\n\nreturn changedItems;"
      },
      "id": "code-compare-estado",
      "name": "Compare Estado Changes",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        720,
        300
      ],
      "notes": "Compares current 'Estado' with 'Estado_Anterior' field. Only passes through records where a state change was detected."
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "conditions": {
          "boolean": [
            {
              "value1": "={{ $json.noChanges }}",
              "value2": true
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "if-has-changes",
      "name": "Has Changes?",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.if",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        940,
        300
      ],
      "notes": "Stops flow if no state changes were detected (noChanges=true goes to false/discard output)."
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rules": {
          "values": [
            {
              "conditions": {
                "options": {
                  "caseSensitive": false,
                  "leftValue": "",
                  "typeValidation": "strict"
                },
                "conditions": [
                  {
                    "leftValue": "={{ $json.estadoActual }}",
                    "rightValue": "Contactado",
                    "operator": {
                      "type": "string",
                      "operation": "equals"
                    }
                  }
                ]
              },
              "renameOutput": "Contactado"
            },
            {
              "conditions": {
